@Node Description "Description"

  Description
  ===========

    Weektop is a *simple* weekly top byte uploader chart.

    It DOES:

    * Auto post messages to the PUBLIC mail base

    * create screen/bulletin files

    * Let the sysop choose how many users are to appear on
      the list

    * Show the user's position in the weektop for the
      last week's weektop.
      (I.e  Position this week = 2 position last week = 5)

    * Tell the sysop what it's doing.

    It does NOT:

    * Work out bytes per user per conf (ie, it's not a conference weektop)

    * Let you change the output style (yet)

    * Display any information to the user (as the carrier will have
      been dropped by the time the door is called)

    See @{"Todo" link ToDo}


@EndNode

@Node Installation "Installation"

  Installation
  ============

    The door is stored as:

    HBBS:Doors/System/WeekTop/WeekTop.HBBS

    This is included and enabled with a fresh installation of HydraBBS
    since V1.10.  Users of prior version should do this:

    Add the following lines to a Commands/System file (HBBS:Commands/System is
    recommended).

    LogOut_Type_1=HBBS
    LogOut_Door_1=HBBS:Doors/System/WeekTop/WeekTop.HBBS {N} <cmddline options>

    InactivityTimeout_Type_1=HBBS
    InactivityTimeout_Door_1=HBBS:Doors/System/WeekTop/WeekTop.HBBS {N} <cmddline options>

    Add the following lines to a Commands/#?Level#? file (HBBS:Commands/All_Levels is
    recommended).

    G_Type_2=HBBS
    G_Door_2=HBBS:Doors/System/WeekTop/WeekTop.HBBS {N} <cmddline options>

    Note: Most HBBS doors use the {O} option in the _Door_ part of the config
    but this door's option are best specified in each place the door can be called
    from.

    Everywhere you see "<cmddline options>" above, you should replace it with
    the actual @{"Command Line Options" link CmdLineOptions}


    Note:
    -----

    As with all HydraBBS door, you can create an alias for the door that can
    be used by the sysop to test it.  Add the following to a
    Commands/Level_255 file:

    WEEKTOPTEST_Type_1=HBBS
    WEEKTOPTEST_Door_1=HBBS:Doors/System/WeekTop/WeekTop.HBBS {N} <cmddline options>

    or

    WEEKTOPTEST_Type_1=HBBS
    WEEKTOPTEST_Door_1=HBBS:Doors/System/WeekTop/WeekTop.HBBS {N} {O}

    If you do the latter you'll be able to specify the paramaters from the command line
    so you can play about with it.

    e.g. If you were at the BBS prompt, you could type in the following

    "WEEKTOPTEST CREATE Ram:TEST 50 NoScreenClear"


@EndNode

