@EndNode

@Node CmdLineOptions "CmdLineOptions"

  Command Line Options
  ====================

    [UPDATE <weekfinalfilename> <users>]
    [CREATE <currentweektopfilename> <users> [NOSCREENCLEAR] [FORCE]]


    This door has two modes of operation, one is just to create the weektop
    file for the current week, the other is to add the current user's
    stats to the weektop data, and generate a weektop final stats file for
    the week is a week has passed since the last one was generated.

    Stats are reset on a monday, or on the first call to the BBS after
    a monday (so it still works if someone calls on a tuesday but
    no-one calls on a monday).  The stats *always* start from a monday
    even if no-one calls on a monday.

    Here are the parameters in detail for the update mode, which must
    be specified before the CREATE mode's parameters.

    UPDATE                   - Specify UPDATE mode
                               This will read the following two parameters
                               from the command line, that *must* be specified
                               Update mode only updated the data file and the
                               weekfinal file.
    <weekfinalfilename>      - Filename to store the updated weektop file as
                               This file is only generated if a week has passed
                               since the last weektop final stats was
                               generated.  This file is also used to generate
                               the mail message that is posted to the public
                               mail base.

    <users>                  - Specifies the amount of users to include in the
                               weektop final file. (Max: 79)


    Here are the parameters in detail for the create mode

    CREATE                   - Specifies CREATE mode
                               This will read in the next two options which
                               must be specified, as well as any optional
                               paramaters.
                               Create mode is used to create the current
                               weektop file.
    <currentweektopfilename> - This specifies the name of the file to store
                               the current week's stats as.
    <users>                  - Specifies the amount of users to include in the
                               current weektop stats file. (Max: 79)
    [NOSCREENCLEAR]          - If this optional paramater is specified then
                               a screen clear will not be present in the
                               output file.
    [FORCE]                  - Force creation of the file.
                               Without this option the current weektop file
                               will only be created if the week has changed
                               or the current user uploaded some files.
    eg:

    UPDATE HBBS:Screens/Bulletins/WeekTop_DEF.TXT 20 CREATE HBBS:Screens/Special/WeekTop_DEF.TXT 15 NoScreenClear


    So in commands/all_levels you'd add:

    G_Type_2=HBBS
    G_Door_2=HBBS:Doors/System/WeekTop/WeekTop.HBBS {N} UPDATE HBBS:Screens/Bulletins/WeekTop_DEF.TXT 20 CREATE HBBS:Screens/Special/WeekTop_DEF.TXT 10

    And in commands/system you'd add:

    LogOut_Type_2=HBBS
    LogOut_Door_2=HBBS:Doors/System/WeekTop/WeekTop.HBBS {N} UPDATE HBBS:Screens/Bulletins/WeekTop_DEF.TXT 20 CREATE HBBS:Screens/Special/WeekTop_DEF.TXT 10

    InactivityTimeOut_Type_1=HBBS
    InactivityTimeOut_Door_1=HBBS:Doors/System/WeekTop/WeekTop.HBBS {N} UPDATE HBBS:Screens/Bulletins/WeekTop_DEF.TXT 20 CREATE HBBS:Screens/Special/WeekTop_DEF.TXT 10

    (note: the above examples assume the BBS has more than one languagename_xx
    defined in BBSGlobal, if you only use one Language_XX then change the
    filenames from "#?_DEF.TXT" to "#?.TXT" (remove the "_DEF" part)

    Here's what you *could* do to have the weektop stats file display to each
    user when they change conferences, using the examples above.

    Create a file called HBBS:Screens/Special/ConfJoined_DEF.TXT so that it
    contains the following line:

    @^@@^PAUSE^@@^SSCREEN^WEEKTOP@

    Using the examples above, when a user joins a conference they will see the
    conference logo, then a pause prompt, then the weektop screen.

    They could also display a bulletin called "WEEKTOP" from the bulletin menu
    (which should be updated, to let the users know there is a new bulletin
    that they can display.

    Please see the following example files:

    HBBS:Storage/Example_Screens/Utopia/Special/ConfJoined_DEF.TXT
    HBBS:Storage/Example_Screens/Special/Bulletins_LIST.TXT
    HBBS:Storage/Example_Configs/Commands/System
    HBBS:Storage/Example_Configs/Commands/All_Levels

@EndNode

